  "title": "Planning Manager (Up to $8800 / 5 days)",
  "description": "<p>Job Title: Planning Manager (ID6058)<br />Location: Depend on project<br />Industry: Construction / Building / Engineering<br />Working Hours: Mon–Fri, 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM<br />Salary: $7800-$8800<br /><br />Roles & Responsibilities<br />1. Coordinate with Costing, M&E, and Business departments on tender requirements and technical support.<br />2. Work with the Construction team on tender planning, EHS matters, and project proposals.<br />3. Attend and assist in subcontractor/supplier meetings related to tenders.<br />4. Review and ensure plans comply with drawings, specifications, and authority requirements.<br />5. Develop Microsoft Project schedules showing full construction sequence from commencement to TOP.<br />6. Propose feasible Temporary Site Facilities and cost-effective ERSS systems.<br />7. Recommend suitable construction sequences for structural and architectural works.<br />8. Review tender documents for discrepancies, value engineering opportunities, and highlight key issues.<br />9. Estimate manpower and resource needs for tender submissions.<br />10. Coordinate with project teams and Japan HQ for construction previews, and support EHS improvement initiatives.<br /><br />Requirement<br />Minimum 12 years of experience in construction site work and planning work</p>",
